],"url":"/#next-steps","content":"Next steps"},"4":{"id":"/-2","page_id":"/","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/","content":"Runyard is a self-hosted control plane for agent runs. Agents and humans trigger workflows over MCP, the CLI, the HTTP API, or the web app; runners execute those workflows with the Smithers engine; and the Hub stores the durable record of everything that happened — runs, logs, events, artifacts, approvals, and knowledge. A run started from a chat agent, a cron schedule, or a terminal all leaves the same auditable trail in the same place."},"5":{"id":"/-3","page_id":"/","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/","content":"Runyard is designed as one private deployment per company. Your Hub holds your workflow catalog, your secrets, your runners, and your history; nothing about your deployment is published to a shared service, and the only outbound call the Hub makes is a passive read of the public GitHub Releases API to check for updates. Operators, teammates, and their agents all authenticate to the same Hub with scoped access tokens."},"6":{"id":"/-4","page_id":"/","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/","content":"Runyard is API-first by construction. Every HTTP route the Hub serves is declared in a single API surface registry; the OpenAPI document is generated from it and the MCP tool list is parity-tested against it. The web app is an ordinary API client with no privileged endpoints — anything it can show or do is equally available over the API and MCP, so a third-party client built on those surfaces loses nothing."},"7":{"id":"/-5","page_id":"/","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/#next-steps","content":"<Card title=\"Quickstart\" href=\"./quickstart\" description=\"Install the Hub, start a runner, and run your first workflow.\" />"},"8":{"id":"/-6","page_id":"/","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/#next-steps","content":"<Card title=\"Concepts\" href=\"./concepts\" description=\"Workflows, runs, runners, approvals, and the Hub's durable record.\" />"},"9":{"id":"/-7","page_id":"/","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/#next-steps","content":"<Card title=\"HTTP API\" href=\"./guides/api\" description=\"Drive Runyard from any language with bearer-token auth and openapi.json.\" />"},"10":{"id":"/-8","page_id":"/","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/#next-steps","content":"<Card title=\"MCP\" href=\"./guides/mcp\" description=\"Connect AI agents to your Hub with the runyard-mcp server.\" />"},"11":{"id":"/quickstart","page_id":"/quickstart","type":"page","content":"Quickstart","breadcrumbs":["Docs"],"tags":[],"url":"/quickstart"},"12":{"id":"/quickstart-0","page_id":"/quickstart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/quickstart","content":"Install the Hub, sign in with the bootstrap token, start a runner, and run the hello workflow."},"13":{"id":"/quickstart-1","page_id":"/quickstart","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/quickstart#1-install-the-hub","content":"1\\. Install the Hub"},"14":{"id":"/quickstart-2","page_id":"/quickstart","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/quickstart#2-sign-in-with-the-bootstrap-token","content":"2\\. Sign in with the bootstrap token"},"15":{"id":"/quickstart-3","page_id":"/quickstart","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/quickstart#3-install-the-cli-and-log-in","content":"3\\. Install the CLI and log in"},"16":{"id":"/quickstart-4","page_id":"/quickstart","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/quickstart#4-start-a-runner","content":"4\\. Start a runner"},"17":{"id":"/quickstart-5","page_id":"/quickstart","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/quickstart#5-run-the-hello-workflow","content":"5\\. Run the hello workflow"},"18":{"id":"/quickstart-6","page_id":"/quickstart","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/quickstart#6-watch-the-run-and-read-the-results","content":"6\\. Watch the run and read the results"},"19":{"id":"/quickstart-7","page_id":"/quickstart","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/quickstart#where-to-go-next","content":"Where to go next"},"20":{"id":"/quickstart-8","page_id":"/quickstart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/quickstart","content":"This page takes you from a fresh Linux box to a completed workflow run with logs and artifacts in the Hub."},"21":{"id":"/quickstart-9","page_id":"/quickstart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/quickstart#1-install-the-hub","content":"The repository's install script is a one-command, idempotent bootstrap. It installs Node 22 and pnpm if needed, clones Runyard at the latest release tag (default `/opt/runyard`), generates an env file with a `SECRETS_ENC_KEY` and session secret, creates the data directory, and installs systemd units for the Hub and a runner:"},"22":{"id":"/quickstart-10","page_id":"/quickstart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/quickstart#1-install-the-hub","content":"Verify the Hub is up:"},"23":{"id":"/quickstart-11","page_id":"/quickstart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/quickstart#1-install-the-hub","content":"The script never prints secrets, never applies updates automatically, and prints a Caddy reverse-proxy snippet if you want TLS in front (recommended for anything non-local — see the security guide)."},"24":{"id":"/quickstart-12","page_id":"/quickstart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/quickstart#2-sign-in-with-the-bootstrap-token","content":"On first boot the Hub writes a full-admin bootstrap token to `bootstrap-token.txt` in its data directory (with the default install, `/opt/runyard/data/bootstrap-token.txt`, mode 600)."},"25":{"id":"/quickstart-13","page_id":"/quickstart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/quickstart#2-sign-in-with-the-bootstrap-token","content":"Open the web app at your Hub URL (for example `https://hub.example.com`) and paste the bootstrap token into the sign-in form. The browser session carries exactly the token's scopes — the bootstrap token is admin, so you can now mint narrower tokens for everything else from the Connect tab."},"26":{"id":"/quickstart-14","page_id":"/quickstart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/quickstart#3-install-the-cli-and-log-in","content":"Each deployment serves its own CLI install script:"},"27":{"id":"/quickstart-15","page_id":"/quickstart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/quickstart#3-install-the-cli-and-log-in","content":"It installs the `runyard` and `runyard-mcp` commands into `~/.local/bin` and prompts for an access token. You can also log in later:"},"28":{"id":"/quickstart-16","page_id":"/quickstart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/quickstart#4-start-a-runner","content":"Runners execute workflows with the Smithers engine, so a runner host needs `bun`, `smithers`, and at least one authenticated agent CLI (`claude`, `codex`, or `pi`) on its PATH."},"29":{"id":"/quickstart-17","page_id":"/quickstart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/quickstart#4-start-a-runner","content":"If you used the Hub install script, a `runyard-runner` systemd unit is already installed and idling. Mint a runner-scoped token, put it in `/etc/runyard/runner.env` as `RUNYARD_HUB_TOKEN=...`, then:"},"30":{"id":"/quickstart-18","page_id":"/quickstart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/quickstart#4-start-a-runner","content":"To run an ad-hoc runner on any other machine (for example your laptop, for `local` execution):"},"31":{"id":"/quickstart-19","page_id":"/quickstart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/quickstart#4-start-a-runner","content":"`runner setup` checks prerequisites and scaffolds the Smithers workspace the runner executes in. Confirm the runner is online:"},"32":{"id":"/quickstart-20","page_id":"/quickstart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/quickstart#5-run-the-hello-workflow","content":"`hello` is a minimal seeded workflow that proves end-to-end execution: it asks the runner's Claude CLI for one sentence and returns structured output."},"33":{"id":"/quickstart-21","page_id":"/quickstart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/quickstart#5-run-the-hello-workflow","content":"Web: open **Workflows**, pick &#x2A;*Hello (Smithers proof)**, fill in `topic`, and click Run."},"34":{"id":"/quickstart-22","page_id":"/quickstart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/quickstart#5-run-the-hello-workflow","content":"CLI:"},"35":{"id":"/quickstart-23","page_id":"/quickstart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/quickstart#5-run-the-hello-workflow","content":"MCP (from any connected agent):"},"36":{"id":"/quickstart-24","page_id":"/quickstart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/quickstart#6-watch-the-run-and-read-the-results","content":"The same data lives at `GET /api/runs/{id}`, `/api/runs/{id}/timeline`, `/api/runs/{id}/logs`, and `/api/runs/{id}/artifacts`, and in the web run page — the Hub is the source of truth even when execution happened on a local runner."},"37":{"id":"/quickstart-25","page_id":"/quickstart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/quickstart#where-to-go-next","content":"Authoring workflows — create your own workflows over the API or MCP."},"38":{"id":"/quickstart-26","page_id":"/quickstart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/quickstart#where-to-go-next","content":"Approvals — put human checkpoints in front of dangerous work."},"39":{"id":"/quickstart-27","page_id":"/quickstart","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/quickstart#where-to-go-next","content":"Agent consumers — point AI agents at your Hub."},"40":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","type":"page","content":"Building agents on Runyard","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Guides"],"tags":[],"url":"/guides/agent-consumers"},"41":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-0","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/agent-consumers","content":"Discovery surfaces, the API-first guarantee, and recommended etiquette for agents and third-party clients."},"42":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-1","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/guides/agent-consumers#discovery-surfaces","content":"Discovery surfaces"},"43":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-2","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/guides/agent-consumers#the-api-first-guarantee","content":"The API-first guarantee"},"44":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-3","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/guides/agent-consumers#auth-expectations","content":"Auth expectations"},"45":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-4","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/guides/agent-consumers#recommended-agent-etiquette","content":"Recommended agent etiquette"},"46":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-5","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/guides/agent-consumers#push-instead-of-poll-response-endpoints","content":"Push instead of poll: response endpoints"},"47":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-6","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/guides/agent-consumers#machine-intake-workflow-endpoints","content":"Machine intake: workflow endpoints"},"48":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-7","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/agent-consumers","content":"Runyard treats agents as first-class API consumers. This page covers how a client discovers what a Hub can do, what it may rely on, and how to be a good citizen."},"49":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-8","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/agent-consumers#discovery-surfaces","content":"Surface"},"50":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-9","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/agent-consumers#discovery-surfaces","content":"Auth"},"51":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-10","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/agent-consumers#discovery-surfaces","content":"What it gives you"},"52":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-11","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/agent-consumers#discovery-surfaces","content":"`GET /llms.txt`"},"53":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-12","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/agent-consumers#discovery-surfaces","content":"none"},"54":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-13","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/agent-consumers#discovery-surfaces","content":"Static, generic orientation for agents: what Runyard is, its tool names, the run path. It deliberately contains nothing deployment-specific and points at the authenticated menu."},"55":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-14","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/agent-consumers#discovery-surfaces","content":"`GET /openapi.json`"},"56":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-15","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/agent-consumers#discovery-surfaces","content":"none"},"57":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-16","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/agent-consumers#discovery-surfaces","content":"The full HTTP surface, generated from the Hub's API surface registry — it cannot drift from the routes the server actually registers."},"58":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-17","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/agent-consumers#discovery-surfaces","content":"MCP `tools/list`"},"59":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-18","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/agent-consumers#discovery-surfaces","content":"token"},"60":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-19","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/agent-consumers#discovery-surfaces","content":"The complete MCP tool set (parity-tested against the API surface). Connect with `runyard mcp install` or the `runyard-mcp` stdio server."},"61":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-20","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/agent-consumers#discovery-surfaces","content":"`GET /api/menu` / `get_menu`"},"62":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-21","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/agent-consumers#discovery-surfaces","content":"token"},"63":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-22","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/agent-consumers#discovery-surfaces","content":"The live, private catalog: workflows with schemas, execution modes, runner pool state, and ready-to-use CLI/MCP invocations."},"64":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-23","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/agent-consumers#discovery-surfaces","content":"Start every session with `get_menu` (or `GET /api/menu`), then `describe_workflow` for anything you intend to run."},"65":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-24","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/agent-consumers#the-api-first-guarantee","content":"The web app is an ordinary client of the same HTTP API, with no privileged endpoints. Every route is declared in one registry that also generates `openapi.json` and is parity-tested against the MCP tool list — so a lossless third-party client is possible by construction: anything the web app can show or do, your client can too, over HTTP or MCP."},"66":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-25","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/agent-consumers#auth-expectations","content":"Ask the Hub's administrator for a scoped access token (admins issue them from the Connect tab or `POST /api/tokens`). Agents typically need `api` and/or `mcp` — nothing more. Send it as `Authorization: Bearer <token>` on every HTTP call, or configure it for the MCP server. Never ask for or expect the bootstrap/admin token."},"67":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-26","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/agent-consumers#recommended-agent-etiquette","content":"**Set `input.title`.** For agent-created runs, include a short human-readable title (\"Audit checkout flow mobile states\") so run lists, approval cards, and human handoff stay decipherable."},"68":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-27","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/agent-consumers#recommended-agent-etiquette","content":"**Preflight first.** When input is rough or unverified, call `preflight_workflow` (`POST /api/workflows/{id}/preflight`) or pass `negotiate: true` to `run_workflow`. You get `ready | needs_input | blocked` with concrete questions and blockers instead of a run that fails."},"69":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-28","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/agent-consumers#recommended-agent-etiquette","content":"**Use run drafts for question/answer loops.** `create_run_draft` creates a proposed run and preflights it; `update_run_draft` merges answers into the input and re-preflights; `submit_run_draft` enqueues the real run only once it is ready; `discard_run_draft` abandons it. Nothing executes until submit."},"70":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-29","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/agent-consumers#recommended-agent-etiquette","content":"**Poll the timeline with `since` cursors.** `get_run_timeline` (`GET /api/runs/{id}/timeline`) returns a unified, ascending view of status transitions, events, and artifacts. Pass the previous response's `nextSince` as `since` so the Hub never re-sends what you have. Fetch results with `get_run_status`, `get_run_logs`, and `get_run_artifacts` / `download_artifact`."},"71":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-30","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/agent-consumers#recommended-agent-etiquette","content":"**Cap what a run may spend.** Pass `budget: { maxTokens, maxCostMicros }` when starting a run; a breach hard-stops the run as the distinct terminal status `budget_exceeded` (never a silent overrun). Read spend as you go from the run's `usage` and `budgetStatus` fields, and use `get_usage_summary` for a fleet rollup. See Usage metering & budgets."},"72":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-31","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/agent-consumers#recommended-agent-etiquette","content":"**Expect paused runs, and resume them.** A run interrupted by exhausted provider credits/quota parks as `paused` instead of failing. Check `run.pause` for the reason and required action, fix it, then `resume_run` (`POST /api/runs/{id}/resume`) — it continues from the engine checkpoint when one exists."},"73":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-32","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/agent-consumers#recommended-agent-etiquette","content":"**Triage with the attention queue.** `list_attention_runs` (`GET /api/runs/attention`) returns everything waiting on a human — paused, awaiting approval, or recently budget-stopped — with counts. Poll it instead of scanning full run lists for stuck work."},"74":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-33","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/agent-consumers#recommended-agent-etiquette","content":"A metered, resumable run end to end:"},"75":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-34","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/agent-consumers#push-instead-of-poll-response-endpoints","content":"`POST /api/workflows/{id}/run` accepts an optional `responseEndpoint` (`{ \"type\": \"http\" | \"telegram\", \"config\": { ... } }`). When the run reaches a terminal state, the Hub POSTs a sanitized payload to your HTTP endpoint (or sends a concise Telegram message). Delivery state is visible on `GET /api/runs/{id}` under `responseEndpoints[]`, and polling remains the canonical fallback."},"76":{"id":"/guides/agent-consumers-35","page_id":"/guides/agent-consumers","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/agent-consumers#machine-intake-workflow-endpoints","content":"For fixed-purpose integrations that should not hold a Hub token at all (webhooks, form intake, external systems), an admin can configure a **workflow endpoint**: `POST /api/workflow-endpoints/{slug}` accepts a payload authenticated with that endpoint's own secret, rate-limited, size-capped, and deduplicated, and triggers exactly one preconfigured workflow. This is the narrowest possible credential to hand to an external system."},"77":{"id":"/guides/api","page_id":"/guides/api","type":"page","content":"HTTP API","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Guides"],"tags":[],"url":"/guides/api"},"78":{"id":"/guides/api-0","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api","content":"Authenticate, discover, and drive workflow runs over the Runyard Hub's HTTP API."},"79":{"id":"/guides/api-1","page_id":"/guides/api","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/guides/api#authentication","content":"Authentication"},"80":{"id":"/guides/api-2","page_id":"/guides/api","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/guides/api#discovery","content":"Discovery"},"81":{"id":"/guides/api-3","page_id":"/guides/api","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/guides/api#api-groups-and-apiv1-aliases","content":"API groups and `/api/v1` aliases"},"82":{"id":"/guides/api-4","page_id":"/guides/api","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/guides/api#the-typical-flow","content":"The typical flow"},"83":{"id":"/guides/api-5","page_id":"/guides/api","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/guides/api#key-endpoints","content":"Key endpoints"},"84":{"id":"/guides/api-6","page_id":"/guides/api","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/guides/api#approvals","content":"Approvals"},"85":{"id":"/guides/api-7","page_id":"/guides/api","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/guides/api#run-drafts","content":"Run drafts"},"86":{"id":"/guides/api-8","page_id":"/guides/api","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/guides/api#error-conventions","content":"Error conventions"},"87":{"id":"/guides/api-9","page_id":"/guides/api","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/guides/api#rate-limits","content":"Rate limits"},"88":{"id":"/guides/api-10","page_id":"/guides/api","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/guides/api#see-also","content":"See also"},"89":{"id":"/guides/api-11","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api","content":"Every Runyard surface — the web app, the CLI, and the MCP server — is an\nordinary client of one HTTP API served by the Hub. Anything they can do, you\ncan do with `curl`."},"90":{"id":"/guides/api-12","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#authentication","content":"Send an access token as a bearer token on every request:"},"91":{"id":"/guides/api-13","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#authentication","content":"Tokens are minted by an admin (web UI, `POST /api/tokens`, or the CLI) and carry\n**scopes**:"},"92":{"id":"/guides/api-14","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#authentication","content":"Scope"},"93":{"id":"/guides/api-15","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#authentication","content":"Grants"},"94":{"id":"/guides/api-16","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#authentication","content":"`api`"},"95":{"id":"/guides/api-17","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#authentication","content":"Start runs, preflight, drafts, rerun/cancel/promote, create approvals"},"96":{"id":"/guides/api-18","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#authentication","content":"`mcp`"},"97":{"id":"/guides/api-19","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#authentication","content":"The same operations, issued for MCP clients"},"98":{"id":"/guides/api-20","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#authentication","content":"`read`"},"99":{"id":"/guides/api-21","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#authentication","content":"**Read-only** — inspect workflows, runs, logs, artifacts, approvals, schedules, and runners; satisfies no mutation endpoint"},"100":{"id":"/guides/api-22","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#authentication","content":"`runner`"},"101":{"id":"/guides/api-23","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#authentication","content":"The runner protocol: register, heartbeat, claim runs, report lifecycle events and artifacts"},"102":{"id":"/guides/api-24","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#authentication","content":"`approvals`"},"103":{"id":"/guides/api-25","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#authentication","content":"Resolve approval cards (approve / reject / request changes) and create them"},"104":{"id":"/guides/api-26","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#authentication","content":"`admin`"},"105":{"id":"/guides/api-27","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#authentication","content":"**Superscope** — satisfies every scope requirement, plus admin-only surfaces: tokens, secrets, audit log, schedules, workflow create/update, packages, hooks, updates"},"106":{"id":"/guides/api-28","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#authentication","content":"`GET /api/tokens/scopes` (admin) returns this vocabulary plus named presets —\n**everything** (`api`+`mcp`+`approvals`, the default), **read-only**,\n**approvals-only**, **runner**, and **admin** — which the Tokens page uses."},"107":{"id":"/guides/api-29","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#authentication","content":"Reads such as listing runs, workflows, or artifacts require any authenticated\ntoken. A token with only the `read` scope is therefore read-only: it can\ninspect everything non-admin but every create/update/delete/run/approve call\nfails with `403`. A request with no valid token gets\n`401 {\"error\": \"unauthorized\"}`; a token missing a required scope gets:"},"108":{"id":"/guides/api-30","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#authentication","content":"with status `403`. `GET /api/me` describes the calling token (name and scopes)."},"109":{"id":"/guides/api-31","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#discovery","content":"**`GET /openapi.json`** (unauthenticated) — generated from the server's API\nsurface registry, the single source of truth every route is registered from,\nso **every endpoint is documented there**. This guide covers the important\nones; use `/openapi.json` for the full list."},"110":{"id":"/guides/api-32","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#discovery","content":"**`GET /api/menu`** (authenticated) — the agent-facing menu: workflow catalog,\nlocal/remote execution modes, and follow-up paths. The same data backs the\nMCP `get_menu` tool and `/llms.txt`."},"111":{"id":"/guides/api-33","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#discovery","content":"**`GET /api/version`** (unauthenticated) — product name, version, instance\nname."},"112":{"id":"/guides/api-34","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#api-groups-and-apiv1-aliases","content":"Operations are organized into eight groups, exposed as OpenAPI tags:\n**workflows**, **runs**, **approvals**, **automation** (schedules + workflow\nendpoints), **library** (agents, skills, knowledge, hooks), **distribution**\n(bundles, packages), **admin** (tokens, secrets, audit, alerts, updates), and\n**system** (health, version, menu, dashboard, runners)."},"113":{"id":"/guides/api-35","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#api-groups-and-apiv1-aliases","content":"Every grouped operation is also reachable at a stable `/api/v1` alias that\nmakes the group visible in the path — for example:"},"114":{"id":"/guides/api-36","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#api-groups-and-apiv1-aliases","content":"Canonical"},"115":{"id":"/guides/api-37","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#api-groups-and-apiv1-aliases","content":"Grouped alias"},"116":{"id":"/guides/api-38","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#api-groups-and-apiv1-aliases","content":"`GET /api/workflows`"},"117":{"id":"/guides/api-39","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#api-groups-and-apiv1-aliases","content":"`GET /api/v1/workflows`"},"118":{"id":"/guides/api-40","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#api-groups-and-apiv1-aliases","content":"`GET /api/runs/:id`"},"119":{"id":"/guides/api-41","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#api-groups-and-apiv1-aliases","content":"`GET /api/v1/runs/:id`"},"120":{"id":"/guides/api-42","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#api-groups-and-apiv1-aliases","content":"`GET /api/run-drafts`"},"121":{"id":"/guides/api-43","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#api-groups-and-apiv1-aliases","content":"`GET /api/v1/runs/drafts`"},"122":{"id":"/guides/api-44","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#api-groups-and-apiv1-aliases","content":"`GET /api/schedules`"},"123":{"id":"/guides/api-45","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#api-groups-and-apiv1-aliases","content":"`GET /api/v1/automation/schedules`"},"124":{"id":"/guides/api-46","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#api-groups-and-apiv1-aliases","content":"`GET /api/agents`"},"125":{"id":"/guides/api-47","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#api-groups-and-apiv1-aliases","content":"`GET /api/v1/library/agents`"},"126":{"id":"/guides/api-48","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#api-groups-and-apiv1-aliases","content":"`GET /api/workflow-bundles`"},"127":{"id":"/guides/api-49","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#api-groups-and-apiv1-aliases","content":"`GET /api/v1/distribution/bundles`"},"128":{"id":"/guides/api-50","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#api-groups-and-apiv1-aliases","content":"`GET /api/tokens`"},"129":{"id":"/guides/api-51","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#api-groups-and-apiv1-aliases","content":"`GET /api/v1/admin/tokens`"},"130":{"id":"/guides/api-52","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#api-groups-and-apiv1-aliases","content":"`GET /api/menu`"},"131":{"id":"/guides/api-53","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#api-groups-and-apiv1-aliases","content":"`GET /api/v1/system/menu`"},"132":{"id":"/guides/api-54","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#api-groups-and-apiv1-aliases","content":"Aliases are the same registry entries registered twice, so they always share\nthe canonical route's handler, auth, and scopes; in `openapi.json` each alias\ncarries `x-canonical-path`. Unversioned `/api/...` paths remain fully\nsupported — use whichever reads better. The legacy `/api/capabilities/*`\npaths are deprecated aliases of `/api/workflows/*` and get no `/api/v1` form;\nnew clients should say *workflow* everywhere."},"133":{"id":"/guides/api-55","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#the-typical-flow","content":"List workflows, preflight your input, start the run, then poll it:"},"134":{"id":"/guides/api-56","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#the-typical-flow","content":"For agent-created runs, include a short human-readable `input.title` — it labels\nrun lists, approval cards, and handoffs. `executionMode` is `local` or `remote`;\n`run` also accepts an optional `responseEndpoint` (`{type: http|telegram,\nconfig}`) to have the terminal-state reply delivered when the run finishes\n(polling `/api/runs/:id` remains the canonical fallback), and an optional\n`budget` (`{maxTokens?, maxCostMicros?}`, also accepted as `input.budget`) that\nhard-caps the run's metered model usage — a breach terminates the run with the\ndistinct status `budget_exceeded`. Metered usage aggregates onto every run\nobject as `usage` and is detailed at `GET /api/runs/:id/usage`; see\nUsage metering & budgets."},"135":{"id":"/guides/api-57","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#the-typical-flow","content":"With `\"negotiate\": true`, a non-ready request returns the negotiation state\n(questions, blockers, warnings, plus a saved draft) instead of creating a run —\nfix the input and call again."},"136":{"id":"/guides/api-58","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#key-endpoints","content":"Workflows and runs (`preflight` and `run` require `api` or `mcp` scope; reads\nrequire any token):"},"137":{"id":"/guides/api-59","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#key-endpoints","content":"Method + path"},"138":{"id":"/guides/api-60","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#key-endpoints","content":"Purpose"},"139":{"id":"/guides/api-61","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#key-endpoints","content":"`GET /api/workflows`"},"140":{"id":"/guides/api-62","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#key-endpoints","content":"List workflows (`?q=` searches)"},"141":{"id":"/guides/api-63","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#key-endpoints","content":"`GET /api/workflows/:id`"},"142":{"id":"/guides/api-64","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#key-endpoints","content":"Describe a workflow and its input schema"},"143":{"id":"/guides/api-65","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#key-endpoints","content":"`GET /api/workflows/:id/source`"},"144":{"id":"/guides/api-66","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#key-endpoints","content":"Workflow source, parsed metadata, sections, graph"},"145":{"id":"/guides/api-67","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#key-endpoints","content":"`POST /api/workflows/:id/preflight`"},"146":{"id":"/guides/api-68","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#key-endpoints","content":"Dry-run preflight: `ready` / `needs_input` / `blocked`, nothing created"},"147":{"id":"/guides/api-69","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#key-endpoints","content":"`POST /api/workflows/:id/run`"},"148":{"id":"/guides/api-70","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#key-endpoints","content":"Run a workflow: `{input, executionMode, negotiate?}`"},"149":{"id":"/guides/api-71","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#key-endpoints","content":"`POST /api/workflows` / `PATCH /api/workflows/:id`"},"150":{"id":"/guides/api-72","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#key-endpoints","content":"Create/update a workflow (admin). Source is submitted as bytes or a `workflow.bundleId` — never a file path"},"151":{"id":"/guides/api-73","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#key-endpoints","content":"`GET /api/runs`"},"152":{"id":"/guides/api-74","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#key-endpoints","content":"List runs (filter by `status`, `q`, `workflow`)"},"153":{"id":"/guides/api-75","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#key-endpoints","content":"`GET /api/runs/:id`"},"154":{"id":"/guides/api-76","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#key-endpoints","content":"Run status, outputs, error, response-delivery state"},"155":{"id":"/guides/api-77","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#key-endpoints","content":"`GET /api/runs/:id/timeline`"},"156":{"id":"/guides/api-78","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#key-endpoints","content":"Unified ascending timeline (`since=<iso>`, `limit=<n>`); backs `runyard tail`"},"157":{"id":"/guides/api-79","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#key-endpoints","content":"`GET /api/runs/:id/usage`"},"158":{"id":"/guides/api-80","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#key-endpoints","content":"Metered usage: aggregate totals, per-call records, budget, and `budgetStop`"},"159":{"id":"/guides/api-81","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#key-endpoints","content":"`GET /api/runs/:id/events` · `/logs` · `/diagnostics`"},"160":{"id":"/guides/api-82","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#key-endpoints","content":"Structured events, log lines, diagnostics + log summary"},"161":{"id":"/guides/api-83","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#key-endpoints","content":"`GET /api/runs/:id/artifacts` · `GET /api/artifacts/:id/download`"},"162":{"id":"/guides/api-84","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#key-endpoints","content":"List a run's artifacts; download bytes"},"163":{"id":"/guides/api-85","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#key-endpoints","content":"`POST /api/runs/:id/cancel` · `/rerun` · `/promote`"},"164":{"id":"/guides/api-86","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#key-endpoints","content":"Cancel; re-queue with same/edited input; merge a successful isolated run into its target branch"},"165":{"id":"/guides/api-87","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#key-endpoints","content":"`POST /api/runs/:id/pause` · `/resume`"},"166":{"id":"/guides/api-88","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#key-endpoints","content":"Park an active run on a recoverable interruption (e.g. `credits_exhausted`; records pause metadata + the engine checkpoint, frees the runner slot); resume re-queues the same run and continues from the checkpoint when one exists"},"167":{"id":"/guides/api-89","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#key-endpoints","content":"Other resources (see `/openapi.json` for the rest — schedules, catalog\nagents/skills/knowledge, hooks, workflow bundles and packages, workflow\nendpoints, runners, dashboard):"},"168":{"id":"/guides/api-90","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#key-endpoints","content":"Method + path"},"169":{"id":"/guides/api-91","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#key-endpoints","content":"Purpose"},"170":{"id":"/guides/api-92","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#key-endpoints","content":"`GET /api/schedules` · `POST /api/schedules`"},"171":{"id":"/guides/api-93","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#key-endpoints","content":"List schedules; create cron/one-shot schedules (admin)"},"172":{"id":"/guides/api-94","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#key-endpoints","content":"`GET /api/runners`"},"173":{"id":"/guides/api-95","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#key-endpoints","content":"Registered runners, heartbeat state, capacity, pool summary"},"174":{"id":"/guides/api-96","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#key-endpoints","content":"`GET /api/tokens` · `POST /api/tokens` · `DELETE /api/tokens/:id`"},"175":{"id":"/guides/api-97","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#key-endpoints","content":"Manage access tokens (admin)"},"176":{"id":"/guides/api-98","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#key-endpoints","content":"`GET /api/secrets` · `PUT /api/secrets/:key` · `DELETE /api/secrets/:key`"},"177":{"id":"/guides/api-99","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#key-endpoints","content":"Encrypted secrets store — names and metadata only, never values (admin)"},"178":{"id":"/guides/api-100","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#key-endpoints","content":"`GET /api/hooks`"},"179":{"id":"/guides/api-101","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#key-endpoints","content":"Post-run hook profiles a workflow may select via `input.postRunHooks`"},"180":{"id":"/guides/api-102","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#key-endpoints","content":"`GET /api/audit`"},"181":{"id":"/guides/api-103","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#key-endpoints","content":"Audit log (admin)"},"182":{"id":"/guides/api-104","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#key-endpoints","content":"`GET /api/dashboard`"},"183":{"id":"/guides/api-105","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#key-endpoints","content":"Run counts by status, recent activity, attention items"},"184":{"id":"/guides/api-106","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#approvals","content":"Workflows can pause on a human decision. Approval cards are first-class API\nobjects (resolving them requires `api`, `mcp`, or `approvals` scope):"},"185":{"id":"/guides/api-107","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#approvals","content":"Method + path"},"186":{"id":"/guides/api-108","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#approvals","content":"Purpose"},"187":{"id":"/guides/api-109","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#approvals","content":"`GET /api/approvals?status=pending`"},"188":{"id":"/guides/api-110","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#approvals","content":"List approval cards (`pending` or `resolved`)"},"189":{"id":"/guides/api-111","page_id":"/guides/api","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/guides/api#approvals","content":"`GET /api/approvals/:id`"},"190":{"id":"