,"Two narrow exceptions authenticate by other means: `POST /api/telegram/webhook` is verified against the configured bot and webhook secret, and `POST /api/workflow-endpoints/{slug}` submissions authenticate with that endpoint's own secret (below). `GET /api/setup` returns only a reduced identity payload (instance name, auth mode) to unauthenticated callers."],[651,"Unclassified failure."],[156,"Unified ascending timeline (`since=<iso>`, `limit=<n>`); backs `runyard tail`"],[669,"Unified timeline: status transitions, events, artifacts as NDJSON."],[318,"Updating a host install"],[678,"Updating a workflow"],[1491,"Updating a workflow bumps its integer `version` and snapshots the previous definition. `GET /api/workflows/{name}/versions` lists the versions observed on past runs, and every run records the `workflowVersion` it executed. Bundle versions count separately, per publish."],[1148,"Usage and budgets"],[1087,"Usage is captured at the **inference boundary**, through two paths:"],[1056,"Usage metering & budgets"],[1058,"Usage records and the run aggregate"],[512,"Use `run_schedule_now` when an external cron or agent should appear as\nScheduled automation in RunYard. Direct `run_workflow` calls keep their\nMCP/token provenance and are not relabeled as scheduled runs."],[1338,"Use for"],[791,"Values"],[290,"Variable"],[408,"Variable"],[429,"Variable"],[22,"Verify the Hub is up:"],[662,"Verify, in order: `TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN` and `TELEGRAM_APPROVAL_CHAT_ID` are set on the Hub; the bot's webhook points at `https://hub.example.com/api/telegram/webhook` with the matching `TELEGRAM_WEBHOOK_SECRET`; the bot is a member of the target chat; and the users pressing buttons are listed in `TELEGRAM_APPROVAL_USER_IDS`. Response-endpoint deliveries record their state (`status`, `attempts`, `last_error`) on `GET /api/runs/{id}` under `responseEndpoints[]`."],[1466,"Versioning"],[520,"Versioning and releases"],[1517,"Versions seen on runs."],[944,"View"],[960,"Visual graph tab."],[637,"Wait and re-run; check the provider account."],[311,"Watch and manage runs"],[249,"Web app"],[33,"Web: open **Workflows**, pick &#x2A;*Hello (Smithers proof)**, fill in `topic`, and click Run."],[243,"Webhook"],[1237,"What a fire produces"],[261,"What each decision does depends on the card's kind:"],[1,"What is Runyard"],[530,"What it does"],[51,"What it gives you"],[725,"What it is"],[883,"What it matches"],[774,"What it represents"],[665,"What it tells you"],[567,"What stays out of public discovery docs"],[691,"What the workflow does; shown in the catalog and menus."],[628,"What to do"],[983,"When an agent hands off to a human — \"approve this\", \"read the logs\" — prefer relaying the payload's deep link over describing where to click."],[857,"When enabled, the daily run queues compact implementation runs sequentially. Each child pushes an isolated review branch targeting `main`; operators inspect and promote the successful branch before `main` changes."],[1175,"When execution is interrupted by a condition a human can fix — the classic case is **the provider account ran out of credits** — the run parks as `paused` instead of failing. Pause metadata lives on `run.pause`:"],[384,"When it finishes it prints next steps: sign in with the bootstrap token, mint a\nrunner-scoped token, put it in `/etc/runyard/runner.env`, and restart the runner\nunit."],[238,"Where approvals appear"],[367,"Where state lives"],[19,"Where to go next"],[620,"Where to look, generally"],[1067,"Where usage appears:"],[1483,"Whether new runs hold for an approval before executing."],[701,"Whether runs hold for a human approval before executing (`{ \"required\": true }`)."],[721,"Who can edit"],[671,"Who did what (admin)."],[135,"With `\"negotiate\": true`, a non-ready request returns the negotiation state\n(questions, blockers, warnings, plus a saved draft) instead of creating a run —\nfix the input and call again."],[797,"With a `fallback` decision (`approve` or `reject`), the configured de